  "text": "Where mIS is the mass of internal standard added to the sample, AIS is the peak area of internal standard, mEE is the mass of the ethyl ester sample and AEE is the peak area of the ethyl ester sample [CITATION_1] . The ethyl ester samples were then analyzed for fuel properties such as kinematic viscosity, density, flash point, cloud point, pour point, acid value and water content as per ASTM methods. ",
